data.title: In Tennessee, Tourists Rediscover The First President Who Was Impeached
data.meta_description: Former President Andrew Johnson's home in Greeneville, Tenn., has seen a recent surge in visitors, similar to a spike observed after former President Bill Clinton was impeached in the late 1990s.
